The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Pak amp; China worries
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Pak amp; China worries
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, Oct. 6: Pakistan and China are modernising their armed forces at a feverish pace and the Centre wants to beef-up military capabilities urgently, defence minister A.K. Antony said today.        
	Antonys observation now indicates the defence ministry is gearing up to sign contracts in the next six months during which the Presidents of the US, Russia and France are expected to visit India.                                                                                                                                                           
